So after reading Jill C.'s ROTD on Indian Curry Bowl, I thought I'd take a drive down, since its minutes away from our house.
I get to the front door and find that  they're CLOSED!?!?!?!
AHHHHHHH!
(Indian Curry Bowls hours are from 11am-9pm, but they close down from 2:30-4pm and open up again for dinner).
Bummin' because I wanted to get my Curry on, I look across the way and see that Smashburger has finally opened their Centennial Center branch, so WTH, I went there to feast on my first Smashburger.
I ordered the 1/3 pound Sin City Smashburger with fried egg, applewood smoked bacon, american cheese grilled onions, haystack onions, and smash sauce which tasted like a blend of mayo and mustard "smashed" together on an egg bun.
I also ordered their sweet potato smashfries(pretty skimpy on the portions) which are tossed with olive oil, rosemary, and garlic, and a frosty mug of IBC root beer.
Smashburger also offers salads, hot dogs, smashchicken burgers and Haagen-Dazs shakes and malts if you happen to be in the mood.
I don't know if they're trying to be a little more "gourmet upscale", but it seems like they're trying to take Hubert Keller's Burger Bar Concept and trying to make it affordable to the masses.
I think for what they give, its pretty pricey, and then they get you on the add-ons.
I could have gotten two #1s at In-n-Out across the street for what I got at Smashburger, and its funny that on the table next to me of 3 people, one guy ordered Smashburger and two of his buddies were eating In-n-Out combosLOL!!!
Next time, In my opinion, If I want fast food, I'll stick to In-n-Out, If I want high end, I'll gladly pay $6 for a little pitcher of Hubert Kellers Black Truffle Sauce to pour on each bite of my custom burger at Burger Bar.....ALOHA!!

